The Herald Midlands Bureau  Police in Gweru are investigating a death incident after a man was found dead in a parked car within Midlands Hotel premises this morning. <img class="size-full wp-image-631400 aligncenter" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2022/07/WhatsApp-Image-2022-07-25-at-1.24.14-PM.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2022/07/WhatsApp-Image-2022-07-25-at-1.24.14-PM.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2022/07/WhatsApp-Image-2022-07-25-at-1.24.14-PM-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" />
The hotel management said the car in which the body was found is a non-runner which has been left parked in the hotel carpark for sometime.  <img class="size-full wp-image-631403 aligncenter" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2022/07/WhatsApp-Image-2022-07-25-at-1.24.14-PM-1.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2022/07/WhatsApp-Image-2022-07-25-at-1.24.14-PM-1.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2022/07/WhatsApp-Image-2022-07-25-at-1.24.14-PM-1-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" />
Midlands provincial police spokesperson Inspector Emmanuel Mahoko said police were at the scene investigating the case.